I‚Äôve often  wondered how my mom is ALWAYS smilingüôÇ ( touchwood) , now I understand it‚Äôs because she has dedicated her self to a life of service and that is the greatest joy one can have.  As the Dalai Lama says, ‚Äú if u are looking for inner peace , do something to help others ‚Äú Happy Mother‚Äôs Day mom üíï

Dr. Mili Shah
Mother, M.S. in Psychotherapy and Counseling¬†

"Being a mother is a blissful experience where kids are your life force. I truly believe mother‚Äôs were the first multitasking superhero‚Äôs who juggle their work life with parenting.¬†

This instinct has helped me be a part of Bisleri Charitable Trust and Ozone Forum of India. This foundation serves many needy patients with the Ozone Therapy and strengthen‚Äôs immunity of our society.¬†

The strength and empathy at my work has followed me due to motherhood. I feel blessed to have such a supporting women staff, mentors and family in this journey."

Heena Mandavia¬†
Mother , Owner of Harsh Thali And Parathas.

@heenamandavia 
@harshthaliandparathas @harsh_mandavia

"Staying true to our tagline, 'Mom Makes, Son Sells', I have been cooking and Harsh has been delivering food for the last 22 years. I think that more than the entrepreneur/chef in me, it is Maa ki mamta, Maa ka dil & mother's empathy that went out to the covid affected people suffering people during the pandemic.¬†

Having been helped by few samaritans / kind strangers in our life during our struggling days to get us where we are today, it is our duty to pay forward the kindness that we have received.

Today,¬† we have raised over 1.5 million INR from 11 countries in donations and fed over 22,000 meals, 55000 rotis, 6000 home made sweets and 800 immunity booster balls¬† to the needy in the past 1 year".

Sunayana Nate.
Mother and Senior Police Inspector , Vakola Police Station

" I thank God for having given me such a position as that of a warrior. It is the best opportunity to serve the public during this crisis.¬†

Really I feel proud to be an officer and mother as well. I love my kids and my duty equally.

I'm grateful for my family members , my colleagues , superiors, friends for supporting and encouraging me.
I do not have any type of fear in my mind and heart, because my motive is always clear towards my work. I always feel joyous in my duty at office and my home."

Priya Chauhan
Mother and Commander, Air India.
@priya.purushotham

"In 2020, when the biggest crises of our lifetime hit mankind, there was no trepidation but to respond to the call of the nation and do my part in helping people return home.

It was a tough time for my young children to understand why their mother would not hug them and always have a mask on. But the thought of people trapped alone,¬† without their loved ones was enough to overcome any anxiety.

While I'm flying today though being mothers day, I'm honoured to have the privilege and opportunity to do my part in this pandemic."

Dr. Snigdha Goel
Mother And Sr. Resident at Safdarjung Hospital, New Delhi.
@suvarcha.gupta

"It‚Äôs overwhelming as a doctor to fulfil your duty towards your profession Inspite of knowing that you are carrying another life within you, who might be at risk due to your commitment. But that‚Äôs what makes you powerful and a believer in God at the end.

I love my profession. I love helping people. It's what I was put on this earth to do. But with the pandemic, its proven to be challenging and a trying time for me just like it is for others too. Coming home to my newly born child and family everyday after work is a blessing.

As we are headed towards celebrating Mother‚Äôs Day, I feel proud and lucky to be bestowed with this special privilege."
